---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro'
import SiteCta from '../components/SiteCta.astro'

const title = 'Veqtor Demo — Review Word Redlines with Claude'
const description = 'Watch Claude use Veqtor with sample Word contract drafts to explain a negotiation, check exact wording, and create a separate counterproposal with tracked changes.'
const videoSchema = {
  '@type': 'VideoObject',
  name: 'Veqtor demo — review Word redlines with Claude',
  description,
  thumbnailUrl: 'https://veqtor.pro/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2-poster.jpg',
  contentUrl: 'https://veqtor.pro/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2.mp4',
  uploadDate: '2026-07-14T00:00:00+03:00',
  duration: 'PT1M44S',
}
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/demo" structuredData={videoSchema}>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Sample contract workflow"
    title="See Claude move from four Word drafts to a reviewable counterproposal."
    lede="The demo uses synthetic documents and normal user prompts. No client data, hidden edits or pre-recorded product responses."
    meta="1 minute 44 seconds · Veqtor v0.1.2 · Sample documents"
    breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Demo' }]}
  >
    <div slot="actions" class="actions"><a class="button button--primary" href="#watch">Play the demo</a><a class="button button--secondary" href="/setup">Connect Veqtor</a></div>
  </PageHero>

  <section class="section section--surface" id="watch" aria-labelledby="video-heading">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Watch</p><h2 id="video-heading">A real Claude session with a disposable negotiation.</h2></div>
        <p>Claude compares the rounds, checks important wording and prepares a separate Word document. The original drafts stay unchanged.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-video">
        <video controls playsinline preload="metadata" poster="/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2-poster.jpg">
          <source src="/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          <track kind="captions" src="/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2.en.vtt" srclang="en" label="English" default />
          Your browser does not support video playback. <a href="/media/veqtor-demo-v0.1.2.mp4">Open the video directly.</a>
        </video>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-caption"><strong>Recorded with Veqtor v0.1.2</strong><span>Claude explains and drafts · Veqtor reads, checks and writes · You review</span></div>
      <p class="demo-install-note">The “one command” line in the narration refers to Claude Code. Claude Desktop currently needs a short configuration edit. One correction: Veqtor 0.1.2 checks the new Word document before saving it; it does not reopen the saved copy for a separate final check.</p>
      <details class="demo-transcript" id="transcript">
        <summary>Read the video transcript</summary>
        <div>
          <p>Claude can reason about a contract, but chat alone cannot reliably inspect several Word drafts or create precise tracked changes. An MCP server gives Claude specialized tools for that work. Claude still does the reasoning. The server performs the document work and returns results we can check against the source.</p>
          <p>Veqtor is an open-source MCP server for Word contract negotiations. It reads redlines, verifies quotations, and creates new drafts with real tracked changes.</p>
          <p>In this demo, I ask what happened to the liability cap across four rounds. Veqtor extracts the tracked revisions. Claude turns the evidence into a clear explanation of how the cap and its carve-outs changed.</p>
          <p>Then I ask for the counterparty's exact latest wording. Instead of relying on the summary, Veqtor checks the quotation against the source file, character for character, and returns the verified text.</p>
          <p>Finally, I turn the review into an action: restore our 150% cap and the willful misconduct carve-out in a new round-five draft. The original stays untouched.</p>
          <p>Veqtor checks every edit before writing, then re-checks the saved file. In this run, no unintended changes. That is MCP in practice: Claude does the reasoning; Veqtor does document work you can verify. It's free, open source, and installs with one command. You're welcome to try it.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--border" aria-labelledby="prompts-heading">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">The prompts</p><h2 id="prompts-heading">Ask in the language of the negotiation.</h2></div>
        <p>You do not need to know how Veqtor works inside. Describe the result you want, and Claude chooses the right step.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prompt-grid">
        <article><span>01 / UNDERSTAND</span><blockquote>“What happened to the limitation of liability across the rounds?”</blockquote><p>Claude explains how the position changed from one draft to the next.</p></article>
        <article><span>02 / CHECK</span><blockquote>“Check the wording you quoted against the counterparty’s change.”</blockquote><p>Veqtor compares the quote with that specific tracked change.</p></article>
        <article><span>03 / RESPOND</span><blockquote>“Prepare our counterproposal in Word with tracked changes.”</blockquote><p>Veqtor tests the requested edits together and creates a separate file for review.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="try-heading">
    <div class="shell prose-shell">
      <article class="prose">
        <p class="eyebrow">Reproduce it</p>
        <h2 id="try-heading">Try the same workflow with fresh sample documents.</h2>
        <p>After connecting Veqtor, create a disposable four-round negotiation in your home folder:</p>
        <div class="code-block" data-copy-layer="technical"><div class="code-block__head"><span>Terminal</span><span>Veqtor 0.1.2</span></div><pre><code>uvx --from "veqtor-mcp==0.1.2" veqtor-demo-rounds ~/veqtor-demo-rounds</code></pre></div>
        <p>Open a new Claude session and ask:</p>
        <blockquote>Using the Veqtor tools, what happened to the limitation of liability across the rounds in ~/veqtor-demo-rounds?</blockquote>
        <p>The sample is safe to discard and recreate. Use it to learn the workflow before pointing Claude at any real matter.</p>
        <div class="notice notice--lime"><strong>Use sample documents first</strong><p>Never include client text, private local paths or activity-history files in a public support request.</p></div>
      </article>
      <aside class="side-index" aria-label="Demo resources">
        <strong>Next</strong>
        <a href="/setup">Connect Veqtor</a>
        <a href="/how-it-works">Understand the workflow</a>
        <a href="/limitations">Read the Alpha limits</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/JohnDeer-ai/veqtor-mcp">View source on GitHub</a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SiteCta title="Ready to reproduce the demo on your computer?" primaryHref="/setup" primaryLabel="Open the connection guide" secondaryHref="/limitations" secondaryLabel="Read the limitations" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .demo-video { background: #030205; border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
  .demo-video video { aspect-ratio: 16/9; display: block; width: 100%; }
  .demo-caption { color: var(--muted); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; font-size: 12px; gap: 12px 24px; justify-content: space-between; padding-top: 14px; }
  .demo-caption strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: var(--weight-title); }
  .demo-install-note { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; margin: 12px 0 0; }
  .demo-transcript { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); margin-top: 28px; }
  .demo-transcript summary { color: var(--muted-strong); cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; padding: 18px 0; }
  .demo-transcript > div { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 840px; padding-bottom: 20px; }
  .demo-transcript p { margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .prompt-grid { border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong); display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  .prompt-grid article { padding: 28px clamp(18px, 3vw, 34px) 8px 0; }
  .prompt-grid article + article { border-left: 1px solid var(--line); padding-left: clamp(18px, 3vw, 34px); }
  .prompt-grid article > span { color: var(--violet); font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: var(--weight-label); }
  .prompt-grid blockquote { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.45; margin: 34px 0 18px; }
  .prompt-grid p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .prompt-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .prompt-grid article { padding: 24px 0; } .prompt-grid article + article { border-left: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-left: 0; } }
</style>
